> Give me the
> choice of shooting myself in the foot if I want to.

Type systems, orthogonal syntax, garbage collection...
Removing this choice is much of what programming language design is about.

I fully agree that having a syntactic integration of regular expressions is a
good idea (via camlp4 of course), but if you want to be able to shoot yourself
in the foot I strongly recommend C++ :-)

-Kenn

